            <title>[SEC-2987] AbstractPreAuthenticatedProcessingFilter should fire a SessionDestroyedEvent when requiresAuthentication invalidates session on principal change</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2987</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Maybe I am missing something but I think that in method &lt;tt&gt;AbstractPreAuthenticatedProcessingFilter.requiresAuthentication&lt;/tt&gt; when session is invalidated because of a principal change a SessionDestroyedEvent should be fired in order to let others, for instance &lt;tt&gt;SessionRegistryImpl&lt;/tt&gt;, do their work&lt;/p&gt;

